DESCRIPTION:Thursday\, March 26\, 2026\, 10:30am - 12:30pm\n\nREACH will be
	 at the library to get to know our patrons and connect them to resources t
	hat they may need.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nInternational District/Chinatown B
	ranch\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed 
	Description: REACH builds relationships with people experiencing homelessn
	ess andconnects them to the help that they need- everything from food and 
	clothing to medical care\, shelter\, and mental health and/or substance us
	e treatment.\, They respond to each client's unique social and clinical ne
	eds. Their work embraces the worth and humanity of the people we serve\, p
	artnering with them to effectively navigate the system.\, Thanks to our pa
	rtner\n\nREACH.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\
	nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide acc
	ommodations for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncont
	actLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.
	All Library programs are free and open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.
	6amcity.com/events/#/details/reach-connecting-people-experiencing-homeless
	ness-with-help-and-resources/17825507/2026-03-26T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Com
